.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::ExternalId \- NIP\-73 External Content IDs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::ExternalId;
\&
\&    # Build i/k tag pairs for an event
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->url_tags(
\&        \*(Aqhttps://myblog.example.com/post/2012\-03\-27/hello\-world\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # $i = [\*(Aqi\*(Aq, \*(Aqhttps://myblog.example.com/post/2012\-03\-27/hello\-world\*(Aq]
\&    # $k = [\*(Aqk\*(Aq, \*(Aqweb\*(Aq]
\&
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->isbn_tags(\*(Aq978\-0\-7653\-8203\-0\*(Aq);
\&    # $i = [\*(Aqi\*(Aq, \*(Aqisbn:9780765382030\*(Aq]  (hyphens stripped)
\&
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->geo_tags(\*(AqEZS42E44YX96\*(Aq);
\&    # $i = [\*(Aqi\*(Aq, \*(Aqgeo:ezs42e44yx96\*(Aq]  (lowercased)
\&
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->country_tags(\*(Aqve\*(Aq);
\&    # $i = [\*(Aqi\*(Aq, \*(Aqiso3166:VE\*(Aq]  (uppercased)
\&
\&    # Optional URL hint (MAY)
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->isan_tags(
\&        \*(Aq0000\-0000\-401A\-0000\-7\*(Aq,
\&        hint => \*(Aqhttps://www.imdb.com/title/tt0120737\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # $i = [\*(Aqi\*(Aq, \*(Aqisan:0000\-0000\-401A\-0000\-7\*(Aq, \*(Aqhttps://www.imdb.com/title/tt0120737\*(Aq]
\&
\&    # Parse an i tag value
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->parse(\*(Aqisbn:9780765382030\*(Aq);
\&    # { type => \*(Aqisbn\*(Aq, value => \*(Aq9780765382030\*(Aq }
\&
\&    # Derive the k tag kind from an i tag value
\&    my $kind = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->kind_for(\*(Aqgeo:ezs42e44yx96\*(Aq);
\&    # \*(Aqgeo\*(Aq
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-73 (External Content IDs). Provides builders for \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR
tag pairs that reference external content identifiers, a parser to
decompose \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tag values, and a helper to derive the \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind.
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tags reference external content IDs. \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tags represent the
external content ID kind so clients can query all events for a specific
kind.
.PP
Each builder normalizes its input per the spec requirements:
.IP \(bu 4
ISBN hyphens are stripped (MUST)
.IP \(bu 4
Geohashes are lowercased (MUST)
.IP \(bu 4
ISO 3166 codes are uppercased (MUST)
.IP \(bu 4
DOI identifiers are lowercased
.IP \(bu 4
Hashtag topics are lowercased
.IP \(bu 4
URL fragments are stripped
.IP \(bu 4
Blockchain transaction IDs are lowercased (hex)
.IP \(bu 4
Ethereum addresses are lowercased (hex)
.PP
Each \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tag MAY include a URL hint as an optional third element to
redirect people to a website if the client isn\*(Aqt opinionated about how
to interpret the id. Pass \f(CW\*(C`hint => $url\*(C'\fR to any builder.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 4
\&    my $id = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->new(
\&        type  => \*(Aqisbn\*(Aq,
\&        value => \*(Aq9780765382030\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::ExternalId\*(C'\fR object. Croaks on unknown
arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS url_tags
.IX Subsection "url_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->url_tags($url, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a URL. Fragments are stripped per the spec.
The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind is \f(CW"web"\fR.
.SS isbn_tags
.IX Subsection "isbn_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->isbn_tags($isbn, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a book ISBN. Hyphens are stripped per the
spec requirement that ISBNs MUST be referenced without hyphens. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR
tag kind is \f(CW"isbn"\fR.
.SS geo_tags
.IX Subsection "geo_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->geo_tags($geohash, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a geohash. The value is lowercased per the
spec requirement that geohashes MUST be lowercase. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind is
\&\f(CW"geo"\fR.
.SS country_tags
.IX Subsection "country_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->country_tags($code, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for an ISO 3166 country or subdivision code
(e.g. \f(CW"VE"\fR, \f(CW"US\-CA"\fR). The code is uppercased per the spec
requirement that ISO 3166 codes MUST be uppercase. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind is
\&\f(CW"iso3166"\fR.
.SS isan_tags
.IX Subsection "isan_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->isan_tags($isan, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a movie ISAN. ISANs SHOULD be referenced
without the version part. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind is \f(CW"isan"\fR.
.SS doi_tags
.IX Subsection "doi_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->doi_tags($doi, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a paper DOI. The DOI is lowercased. The
\&\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind is \f(CW"doi"\fR.
.SS hashtag_tags
.IX Subsection "hashtag_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->hashtag_tags($topic, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a hashtag. The topic is lowercased. The
\&\f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR value is prefixed with \f(CW\*(C`#\*(C'\fR. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind is \f(CW"#"\fR.
.SS podcast_feed_tags
.IX Subsection "podcast_feed_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->podcast_feed_tags($guid, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a podcast RSS feed GUID. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind
is \f(CW"podcast:guid"\fR.
.SS podcast_episode_tags
.IX Subsection "podcast_episode_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->podcast_episode_tags($guid, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a podcast RSS item GUID. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind
is \f(CW"podcast:item:guid"\fR.
.SS podcast_publisher_tags
.IX Subsection "podcast_publisher_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->podcast_publisher_tags($guid, hint => $hint);
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a podcast RSS publisher GUID. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag
kind is \f(CW"podcast:publisher:guid"\fR.
.SS blockchain_tx_tags
.IX Subsection "blockchain_tx_tags"
.Vb 3
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->blockchain_tx_tags(
\&        $blockchain, $txid, chain_id => $chain_id, hint => $hint,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a blockchain transaction. \f(CW$blockchain\fR
is the chain name (e.g. \f(CW"bitcoin"\fR, \f(CW"ethereum"\fR). \f(CW$txid\fR is
lowercased (hex). If \f(CW\*(C`chain_id\*(C'\fR is provided (e.g. for Ethereum), it is
included in the identifier. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind is \f(CW"$blockchain:tx"\fR.
.SS blockchain_address_tags
.IX Subsection "blockchain_address_tags"
.Vb 3
\&    my ($i, $k) = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->blockchain_address_tags(
\&        $blockchain, $address, chain_id => $chain_id, hint => $hint,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Returns \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag pair for a blockchain address. Bitcoin base58
addresses are case\-sensitive; Bitcoin bech32 and Ethereum hex addresses
are lowercase. If \f(CW\*(C`chain_id\*(C'\fR is provided, it is included in the
identifier. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind is \f(CW"$blockchain:address"\fR.
.SS parse
.IX Subsection "parse"
.Vb 1
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->parse($i_tag_value);
.Ve
.PP
Parses an \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tag value and returns a hashref with \f(CW\*(C`type\*(C'\fR (the \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag
kind) and \f(CW\*(C`value\*(C'\fR (the extracted identifier). For blockchain types,
\&\f(CW\*(C`blockchain\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`chain_id\*(C'\fR are also included. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for
unrecognized formats.
.SS kind_for
.IX Subsection "kind_for"
.Vb 1
\&    my $kind = Net::Nostr::ExternalId\->kind_for($i_tag_value);
.Ve
.PP
Returns the \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind string for a given \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tag value. This is a
convenience wrapper around "parse". Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized
formats.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS type
.IX Subsection "type"
The external content ID type (\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag kind value).
.SS value
.IX Subsection "value"
The extracted identifier value.
.SS blockchain
.IX Subsection "blockchain"
The blockchain name (for blockchain types only).
.SS chain_id
.IX Subsection "chain_id"
The chain ID (for blockchain types with a chain ID, e.g. Ethereum).
.SS hint
.IX Subsection "hint"
An optional URL hint.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-73 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/73.md>,
Net::Nostr, Net::Nostr::Metadata
